    },
    {
      "_id": "6976f972ff45f16b",
      "name": "Damage Vulnerability",
      "sort": 12,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80a6-a30b-d09215c4ed04\"><em><strong>Vulnerability</strong></em><em><strong> </strong></em><em><strong>(X):</strong></em> Increase damage taken by X each time the creature takes damage of that type.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8046-830a-ccae3dac0f4a\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example:</strong> If you had <strong>Poison</strong><strong> Vulnerability</strong><strong> (2)</strong> and took <strong>3</strong> Poison damage, you would instead take <strong>4</strong> Poison damage (you add 1 to the Poison damage taken, so 3 + 2 = 5).</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8043-9ac0-e1c4b82af68a\"><em><strong>Vulnerability (Double):</strong></em> Increases the Damage taken by 2 times of the specified type.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-805d-b219-c501ab294a30\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example:</strong> If a Werewolf has <strong>Vulnerability </strong><strong>(Double)</strong><strong> </strong>to Silvered Weapons and takes <strong>5</strong> damage from an Attack, they would instead take <strong>10 </strong>damage (5 x 2 = 10).</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
