    {
      "_id": "3f98acac6d59ed64",
      "name": "Multiple Damage Types",
      "sort": 22,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-809a-9bc6-fc05be00fac4\" class=\"block-color-default_background\">When you take multiple types of damage that you have Resistances (or Vulnerabilities) to, you apply your Resistances (or Vulnerabilities) to each damage type individually.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80f6-8ebb-fc77f206d7c2\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example: </strong>You have Physical Resistance (Half) from PDR granted by Armor and take <strong>3</strong> Piercing damage and <strong>3</strong> Slashing damage from an Attack. The Piercing damage would be reduced by half to 1.5, then rounded up to <strong>2</strong> damage taken. The same would be true of the Slashing damage (<strong>2</strong> damage taken). You would take a total of <strong>4</strong> damage from the Attack.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "category": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "exportSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.350",
